summary: And again, there's a Jonsa reunion scene, there's a Jon losing Yggritte scene, and absolutely no Jon3rys scene. And it was a...
body:
And again, there’s a Jonsa reunion scene, there’s a Jon losing Yggritte scene, and absolutely no Jon3rys scene. And it was a teaser completely made with previous seasons’ scenes. It’s almost like… Jon3rys scenes… were so unimportant to even mention. I almost feel sorry for Jon3rys stans😂

Instead, we get Jon vs Daenerys vs Cersei as three sides of power warring for the throne. And the last shot of Jon with a dragon roaring behind him (Daenerys nowhere to be seen), clearly a reference to him being the heir to the throne.

title: Game of Thrones ya tiene fecha de estreno para su octava temporada
body:
Game of Thrones ya tiene fecha de estreno para su octava temporada

HBO terminó el suspenso y confirmó el mes en que serán estrenados los últimos capítulos de la serie que recrea una batalla de familias por un trono.

“Hay una sola batalla que importa y está aquí”. Con esa frase Jon Snow da paso al anuncio de la fecha de estreno de la octava y última temporada de “Game of Thrones”.

A más de un año de que se estrenara la séptima entrega, HBO finalmente terminó…

summary: What are the chances that GRRM is allowing D&D to spoil who gets on the throne (hence the hashtag #ForTheThrone) without...
body:
What are the chances that GRRM is allowing D&D to spoil who gets on the throne (hence the hashtag #ForTheThrone) without spoiling the “fantasy” side of the story (WW, azor ahai, etc) so GRRM can save that element for the books?

Because it’s weird that they’re making the final season about the Iron Throne when Jon just spent seven seasons explaining to everyone willing to listen how the thing that matters isn’t the Throne but rather the war with The Others.

Is HBO trying to distract us? Or doing a favor for GRRM so that his story doesn’t get completely told before the final books?
